  "texts": [
    "29 It might be possible to explicitly derive the equivalence of these two covering map definitions using the techniques of section 5.1.",
    "To do so, one could realise sl(2, R)1 ⊕ u(1) using the fields (β, γ, ξ +, η-), where η-= -e -ϕ 2 -iκ 2 ∂(ϕ1+ 1 2 ϕ2 + 3 2 iκ2), before deriving F γξ + = FγF ξ +.",
    "The equivalence of definitions then immediately follows from γξ + = -ξ -.",
    "We are yet to verify the factorisation of the path integral, explicitly checking the Jacobian from the change of basis and how the vertex operators factorise into pieces that depend independently on γ and ξ +.",
    "JHEP04(2024)048at the zeroes of ω + (z) for z ∈ Σ g /{z i, u α: i = 1, 2,..., n; α = 1, 2,... n -2 + 2g}."
